==English==
===Etymology===
From German ''[[verboten#German|verboten]]'' "forbidden".
===Adjective===
'''verboten'''

# [[forbidden]], [[prohibited]]
===Usage note===
A loanword with connotations of state [[authoritarianism]], derived from a perception of the German Empire under [[w:Wilhelm II|Wilhelm II]] or [[w:Nazi|Nazi]] Germany. Contemporary usage may be jocular.
